article.headline: S. Utah 66, UMKC 50
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- Davis Baker and Tyler Quinney scored 24 points each Saturday to lead Southern Utah to a 66-50 Summit League win over Missouri-Kansas City. For the Thunderbirds (5-11, 3-2 Summit League) it was their first road win out of nine so far this season. The Kangaroos (5-13, 1-4) lost their fifth straight. Southern Utah led 34-32 with 15 minutes to play before outscoring the Kangaroos 32-18 for the rest of the game. Dane Brumagin led UMKC with 20 points, while Spencer Johnson had a game-high 12 rebounds. John Clifford had 11 rebounds for the Thunderbirds. Southern Utah was 16-of-18 at the free throw line and hit 24-of-49 from the floor. The Kangaroos hit just 31 percent from the field on 16-of-52.
